DAY 2 - ORDER BY

ORDER BY is used to sort data.

Ascending Order (Small to Large)

SELECT * FROM students
ORDER BY age;

Descending Order (Large to Small)

SELECT * FROM students
ORDER BY age DESC;

Important:

ORDER BY = Sort data

DESC = Largest to smallest



SQL Practice (First Query Writing)

Look at this table:

id	name	age
1	Ishu	21
2	Ram	25
3	Priya	20

Write the SQL query for:

SQL Question 1

Show only the name column.

SQL Question 2

Show all students whose age is 25.

SQL Question 3

Show all students sorted by age from largest to smallest.



1.SELECT name FROM students;

2.SELECT * FROM students WHERE age = 25;

3. SELECT * FROM students ORDER BY age DESC;

